=begin slide 
=title Hypothesis

Young people interested in careers involved with science, mathematics,
engineering, or almost any technical field should be introduced to
B<Linux>.
=end slide 

=begin slide 
=title What is Linux?
=subtitle Part 1

More formally known as B<GNU/Linux> ,
it's a free operating system (OS) invented by Linus Torvald to
provide a UNIX-like system with all the standard
command-line and graphical tools that accompany
such a system.

B<Linux>, rather than Windows or Mac, provides much of the
I<behind-the-scenes cloud> computing in data centers and
*high-performance computing facilities. It also powers the Android and
I<the Internet of Things>* (IoT).
=end slide 

=begin slide 
=title What is Linux?
=subtitle Part 2

A more detailed look:

L<https://www.lifewire.com/basic-guide-linux-operating-system-2202786>
=end slide 

=begin slide 
=title What is Linux?
=subtitle Part 3

The command-line environment provides the user with almost complete
freedom to automate tasks typical in research or other work or study
in technical fields.

B<Linux> also gives the user much greater control over what happens
and what does not happen on his or her computer.
=end slide 

=begin slide 
=title Linux vs. Windows: Windows

Windows:

=item Is everywhere

=item Is primarily a GUI operation

=item Is expensive

=item B<Hides internals>

=item B<Has a non-case-sensitive file system>

=item Updates when Microsoft says it should, often restarting your
computer without your permission.
=end slide 


=begin slide 
=title Linux vs. Windows: Linux

Linux:

=item Is pretty much the opposite of Windows in most respects

=item Is everywhere, although it is usually working behind the scenes

=item Has both GUI and intrinsic command line capabilities

=item B<Is FREE>

=item Shows as much or as little of the internals as you want to see

=item Has a case-sensitive file system

=item B<Performs upgrades only if you want it to>

=item Is unparalleled for the scientist or engineers: a powerful,
"programmable calculator"
=end slide 

